onor can overflow its outer lobe. Our results indicate\nthat mass transfer is stable for a wider range of binary parameter space than\ntypically assumed in rapid binary population synthesis and found in recent\nsimilar studies. Moreover, we find a systematic dependence of the critical mass\nratio on the donor star mass and radius which may have significant consequences\nfor predictions of post-mass-transfer populations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Sep 2022 14:02:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 31 Oct 2022 16:54:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-11"}
